32int
33GenericAppIdDecoder::ExtractNumeric(const BitArray& bits, int pos, int count)
34{
35 int value = 0;
36 auto bitIter = bits.iterAt(pos);
37 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i, ++bitIter) {
38 value = (value << 1) | static_cast<int>(*bitIter);
39 }
40 return value;
41}

135static bool
136IsStillAlpha(const BitArray& bits, int pos)
137{
138 if (pos + 5 > bits.size()) {
139 return false;
140 }
141
142 // We now check if it's a valid 5-bit value (0..9 and FNC1)
143 int fiveBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 5);
144 if (fiveBitValue >= 5 && fiveBitValue < 16) {
145 return true;
146 }
147
148 if (pos + 6 > bits.size()) {
149 return false;
150 }
151
152 int sixBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 6);
153 return sixBitValue >= 16 && sixBitValue < 63; // 63 not included
154}

156static bool
157IsStillIsoIec646(const BitArray& bits, int pos)

160 return false;

165 return true;

174 return true;

177 if (pos + 8 > bits.size()) {
178 return false;
179 }
180
181 int eightBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 8);
182 return eightBitValue >= 232 && eightBitValue < 253;
183}

185static bool
186IsStillNumeric(const BitArray& bits, int pos)
187{
188 // It's numeric if it still has 7 positions
189 // and one of the first 4 bits is "1".
190 if (pos + 7 > bits.size()) {
191 return pos + 4 <= bits.size();
192 }
193 auto bitIter = bits.iterAt(pos);
194 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i, ++bitIter) {
195 if (*bitIter) {
196 return true;
197 }
198 }
199 return false;
200}

202static DecodedChar
203DecodeAlphanumeric(const BitArray& bits, int pos)
204{
205 int fiveBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 5);
206 if (fiveBitValue == 15) {
207 return DecodedChar(pos + 5, DecodedChar::FNC1);
208 }
209
210 if (fiveBitValue >= 5 && fiveBitValue < 15) {
211 return DecodedChar(pos + 5, (char)('0' + fiveBitValue - 5));
212 }
213
214 int sixBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 6);
215
216 if (sixBitValue >= 32 && sixBitValue < 58) {
217 return DecodedChar(pos + 6, (char)(sixBitValue + 33));
218 }
219
220 if (sixBitValue < 58 || sixBitValue > 62)
221 throw std::runtime_error("Decoding invalid alphanumeric value");
222
223 constexpr char const* lut58to62 = R"(*,-./)";
224 char c = lut58to62[sixBitValue - 58];
225
226 return DecodedChar(pos + 6, c);
227}

229static bool
230IsAlphaTo646ToAlphaLatch(const BitArray& bits, int pos)
231{
232 if (pos + 1 > bits.size()) {
233 return false;
234 }
235 for (int i = 0; i < 5 && i + pos < bits.size(); ++i) {
236 if (i == 2) {
237 if (!bits.get(pos + 2)) {
238 return false;
239 }
240 }
241 else if (bits.get(pos + i)) {
242 return false;
243 }
244 }
245 return true;

282static DecodedInformation
283ParseAlphaBlock(const BitArray& bits, ParsingState& state, std::string& buffer)
284{
285 while (IsStillAlpha(bits, state.position)) {
286 DecodedChar alpha = DecodeAlphanumeric(bits, state.position);
287 state.position = alpha.newPosition;
288
289 if (alpha.isFNC1()) {
290 return DecodedInformation(state.position, buffer); //end of the char block
291 }
292 buffer.push_back(alpha.value);
293 }
294
295 if (IsAlphaOr646ToNumericLatch(bits, state.position)) {
296 state.position += 3;
297 state.encoding = ParsingState::NUMERIC;
298 }
299 else if (IsAlphaTo646ToAlphaLatch(bits, state.position)) {
300 if (state.position + 5 < bits.size()) {
301 state.position += 5;
302 }
303 else {
304 state.position = bits.size();
305 }
306 state.encoding = ParsingState::ISO_IEC_646;
307 }
308 return DecodedInformation();
309}

311static DecodedChar
312DecodeIsoIec646(const BitArray& bits, int pos)
313{
314 int fiveBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits,pos, 5);
315 if (fiveBitValue == 15) {
316 return DecodedChar(pos + 5, DecodedChar::FNC1);
317 }
318
319 if (fiveBitValue >= 5 && fiveBitValue < 15) {
320 return DecodedChar(pos + 5, (char)('0' + fiveBitValue - 5));
321 }
322
323 int sevenBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 7);
324
325 if (sevenBitValue >= 64 && sevenBitValue < 90) {
326 return DecodedChar(pos + 7, (char)(sevenBitValue + 1));
327 }
328
329 if (sevenBitValue >= 90 && sevenBitValue < 116) {
330 return DecodedChar(pos + 7, (char)(sevenBitValue + 7));
331 }
332
333 int eightBitValue = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 8);
334 if (eightBitValue < 232 || eightBitValue > 252)
335 throw std::runtime_error("Decoding invalid ISO-IEC-646 value");
336
337 constexpr char const* lut232to252 = R"(!"%&'()*+,-./:;<=>?_ )";
338 char c = lut232to252[eightBitValue - 232];
339
340 return DecodedChar(pos + 8, c);
341}

343static DecodedInformation
344ParseIsoIec646Block(const BitArray& bits, ParsingState& state, std::string& buffer)
345{
346 while (IsStillIsoIec646(bits, state.position)) {
347 DecodedChar iso = DecodeIsoIec646(bits, state.position);
348 state.position = iso.newPosition;
349 if (iso.isFNC1()) {
350 return DecodedInformation(state.position, buffer);

353 }

356 state.position += 3;;
357 state.encoding = ParsingState::NUMERIC;
358 }
359 else if (IsAlphaTo646ToAlphaLatch(bits, state.position)) {
360 if (state.position + 5 < bits.size()) {
361 state.position += 5;
362 }
363 else {
364 state.position = bits.size();
365 }
366 state.encoding = ParsingState::ALPHA;
367 }
368 return DecodedInformation();

371static DecodedNumeric
372DecodeNumeric(const BitArray& bits, int pos)
373{
374 if (pos + 7 > bits.size()) {
375 int numeric = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 4);
376 if (numeric == 0) {
377 return DecodedNumeric(bits.size(), DecodedNumeric::FNC1, DecodedNumeric::FNC1);
378 }
379 return DecodedNumeric(bits.size(), numeric - 1, DecodedNumeric::FNC1);
380 }
381 int numeric = ExtractNumeric(bits, pos, 7);
382 int digit1 = (numeric - 8) / 11;
383 int digit2 = (numeric - 8) % 11;
384
385 return DecodedNumeric(pos + 7, digit1, digit2);
386}

388static DecodedInformation
389ParseNumericBlock(const BitArray& bits, ParsingState& state, std::string& buffer)
390{
391 while (IsStillNumeric(bits, state.position)) {
392 DecodedNumeric numeric = DecodeNumeric(bits, state.position);
393 state.position = numeric.newPosition;
394
395 if (numeric.isFirstDigitFNC1()) {
396 DecodedInformation information;
397 if (numeric.isSecondDigitFNC1()) {
398 return DecodedInformation(state.position, buffer);
399 }
400 else {
401 return DecodedInformation(state.position, buffer, numeric.secondDigit);
402 }
403 }
404
405 buffer.append(std::to_string(numeric.firstDigit));
406 if (numeric.isSecondDigitFNC1()) {
407 return DecodedInformation(state.position, buffer);
408 }
409 buffer.append(std::to_string(numeric.secondDigit));
410 }
411
412 if (IsNumericToAlphaNumericLatch(bits, state.position)) {
413 state.encoding = ParsingState::ALPHA;
414 state.position += 4;
415 }
416 return DecodedInformation();
417}

420static DecodedInformation
421ParseBlocks(const BitArray& bits, ParsingState& state, std::string& buffer)
422{
423 while (true) {
424 int initialPosition = state.position;
425 auto result =
426 state.encoding == ParsingState::ALPHA ?
427 ParseAlphaBlock(bits, state, buffer) :
428 (state.encoding == ParsingState::ISO_IEC_646 ?
429 ParseIsoIec646Block(bits, state, buffer) :
430 // else
431 ParseNumericBlock(bits, state, buffer));
432 if (result.isValid() || initialPosition == state.position)
433 {
434 return result;
435 }
436 }
